SIMPLE: share
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Share
<hw>Share</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>schar</ets>,
AS. <ets>scear</ets>; akin to OHG. <ets>scaro</ets>, G.
<ets>schar</ets>, pflug<ets>shar</ets>, and E. <ets>shear</ets>, v. See
<er>Shear</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The part (usually an iron or
steel plate) of a plow which cuts the ground at the bottom of a furrow;
a plowshare.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The part which opens the ground for the reception of
the seed, in a machine for sowing seed.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Share</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Share
<hw>Share</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>share</ets>, AS.
<ets>scearu</ets>, <ets>scaru</ets>, fr. <ets>sceran</ets> to shear,
cut. See <er>Shear</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A certain
quantity; a portion; a part; a division; <as>as, a small <ex>share</ex>
of prudence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Especially, the part allotted or belonging to one,
of any property or interest owned by a number; a portion among others;
an apportioned lot; an allotment; a dividend.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧My
<xex>share</xex> of fame.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hence, one of a certain number of equal portions
into which any property or invested capital is divided; <as>as, a ship
owned in ten <ex>shares</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The pubes; the sharebone.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To go shares</b></col>, <cd>to partake; to be equally
concerned.</cd> -- <col><b>Share and share alike</b></col>, <cd>in equal
shares.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Share</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Share
<hw>Share</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Shared</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sharing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To part among two or
more; to distribute in portions; to divide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Suppose I <qex>share</qex> my fortune equally between my children
and a stranger.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1324 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To partake of, use, or experience, with others; to
have a portion of; to take and possess in common; <as>as, to
<ex>share</ex> a shelter with another</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>While avarice and rapine share</qex> the land.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To cut; to shear; to cleave; to divide.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>shared</qex> visage hangs on equal sides.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Share</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Share
<hw>Share</hw> <pr>(sh⟦acir⟧r)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To have part;
to receive a portion; to partake, enjoy, or suffer with
others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A right of inheritance gave every one a title to <qex>share</qex>
in the goods of his father.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sharebeam</ent>⟦br⟧
